# Add Dark Mode Toggle and Copy Code Button to Documentation

## Summary

This PR adds two user experience improvements to the Lodash documentation site:
1. **Dark Mode Toggle** - A fixed-position button that allows users to switch between light and dark themes
2. **Copy Code Button** - One-click copy-to-clipboard functionality for all code examples

Both features improve developer experience and accessibility when reading documentation for extended periods.

## Features

### 🌙 Dark Mode Toggle
- Fixed-position button in the top-right corner
- Persists user preference in `localStorage`
- Respects system preference (`prefers-color-scheme`) on first visit
- Smooth transitions between light and dark themes
- Comprehensive dark theme styling for all documentation elements

### 📋 Copy Code Button
- Appears on hover over code blocks
- One-click copy to clipboard using modern Clipboard API
- Fallback support for older browsers
- Visual feedback (checkmark icon) after successful copy
- Accessible with proper ARIA labels
- Works seamlessly in both light and dark modes

## Implementation Details

### New Functions Added

#### 1. `addCopyButtons()` Function

This function adds copy buttons to all code blocks in the documentation:

```javascript
/**
 * Adds copy buttons to code blocks.
 *
 * @private
 * @param {Object} $ The Cheerio object.
 */
function addCopyButtons($) {
  let codeBlockIndex = 0;
  $('.highlight').each(function() {
    const $highlight = $(this);
    const $pre = $highlight.find('pre').first();
    if ($pre.length) {
      codeBlockIndex++;
      const codeId = `code-block-${codeBlockIndex}`;
      $pre.attr('id', codeId);
      
      // Create copy button
      const $copyButton = $('<button>')
        .addClass('copy-code-btn')
        .attr('data-clipboard-target', `#${codeId}`)
        .attr('aria-label', 'Copy code')
        .html('<svg>...</svg>');
      
      // Wrap highlight in a container for positioning
      if (!$highlight.parent().hasClass('code-block-wrapper')) {
        $highlight.wrap('<div class="code-block-wrapper"></div>');
      }
      $highlight.after($copyButton);
    }
  });
}
```

#### 2. `addDarkModeToggle()` Function

This function adds the dark mode toggle button to the page:

```javascript
/**
 * Adds dark mode toggle button and styles.
 *
 * @private
 * @param {Object} $ The Cheerio object.
 */
function addDarkModeToggle($) {
  // Create dark mode toggle button
  const $toggle = $('<button>')
    .addClass('dark-mode-toggle')
    .attr('aria-label', 'Toggle dark mode')
    .attr('title', 'Toggle dark mode')
    .html('<svg>...</svg>');
  
  // Add dark mode toggle button at the beginning of body
  const $body = $('body');
  if ($body.length) {
    $body.prepend($toggle);
  } else {
    // If no body tag, add to the root
    const $root = $('*').first();
    $root.prepend($toggle);
  }
}
```

### Integration into Build Process

Both functions are called during the HTML generation process:

```javascript
// Cleanup highlights.
tidyHighlights($);
// Add copy buttons to code blocks.
addCopyButtons($);
// Add dark mode toggle.
addDarkModeToggle($);
```

### CSS and JavaScript Injection

The build script injects comprehensive CSS styles and JavaScript functionality:

**CSS Features:**
